 ## 7. Rebuilding GNOME OS with your changes and deploying them
 
-While it's possible to rebuild the GNOME OS images on each change and reinstall them each time you make changes, this leads to a very slow iteration cycle and is not recommended. Instead, use the `systemd-sysext` and/or `systemd-sysupdate` workflows described in the following section to build and deploy your changes to your local workstation, VM or a different machine in a much faster way.
